Background
Responsibilities
Scope of work:
The Compliance Analyst will serve as point-of-contact for the Compliance and Ethics Department and provide support to the existing Compliance team, primarily in the area of compliance due diligence, and will assist with special projects as required by the Compliance Manager in US/India. Essential duties and responsibilities: Managing the Compliance due diligence process including conducting Due Diligence on potential representatives (JV partners, agents, distributors, consultants etc.), customers, vendors, suppliers, employees and other third-parties. Analyzing information from multiple documents and sources related to the due diligence subject and raising red flags when identified.
Liaising with various internal stakeholders in ensuring timely/accurate completion of the due diligence process. Communicating due diligence results to the business and providing suitable advice/recommendations. Maintaining all applicable Due Diligence tracking databases and producing reports and statistics on the same. Assist in the implementation of new processes and new technology to assist in the due diligence process. Serve as the Compliance functions main point of contact with external due diligence providers and vendors. Keeping abreast of changing regulations, particularly those related to Anti-bribery and Corruption. Providing training to internal staff on the due diligence process, when needed. Providing support on ad-hoc projects, including Assurance Function Site Assessments. Very good oral, written, and interpersonal communication skills.
Very good organizational skills, ability to prioritize, and workload flexibility.
Interpersonal Skills:
Ability to interface with internal and external customers as needed Ability to read, analyze, and interpret data from multiple sources Ability to write in a clear and concise manner Ability to effectively present information and respond to questions Willingness and ability to train and teach other less experienced teams
